topic name :- create an ebs volume and mount on ec2 instance
  
  1  -  go to ec2 > launch instance > 

  2  -  click volume > create volume

  3  -  give name and click to create volume 

  4  -  select created volume > action > attach volume
   
  5  -  go to moboxterm and take ssh of instance 

  6  -  lsblk > fdisk /dev/xvdf

  7  -  sudo mkfs -t xfs /dev/xvdf

  8  -  sudo mkdir -p /mount/volume/new volume

  9  -  mount volume on this path > type sudo mount /dev/xvdf/mount/volume/new volume

  10 - df -h

  11 -  mounting success
